    "body": "Fixes: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25857\r\n\r\nAdd a new `'syncoutput'` option that, when set, enables [Synchronized Output][1] mode, if supported by the terminal. The implementation first issues a DECRQM escape sequence to query the terminal for synchronized output support. If the terminal supports it, then synchronized output is controlled by the `'syncoutput'` setting.\r\n\r\nWhen `'syncoutput'` is enabled (and supported by the terminal) then all screen updates done by Nvim are buffered/batched together to be displayed by the terminal emulator at once. This eliminates flickering/tearing in cases when the terminal emulator updates the screen faster than Nvim can draw it.\r\n\r\nThis PR also refactors some of the CSI event handling in `tui/input.c`. It is currently used only for handling kitty keyboard protocol queries, but since we are adding more things to this stick (see also https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/25868) it is nice to go ahead and clean it up a little bit.\r\n\r\n- refactor(input): move CSI event handling into a dedicated function\r\n- feat(tui): add 'syncoutput' option\r\n\r\n[1]: https://gist.github.com/christianparpart/d8a62cc1ab659194337d73e399004036\r\n",
